Credential: ./credential
Share Context: Wordpress Context
Param: user_id: the id of the user to get

#!/usr/bin/env python3 ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/main.py GetUser

---
Name: List Posts
Description: List posts in wordpress site
Credential: ./credential
Share Context: Wordpress Context
Param: context: the context of the posts to list, must be one of: view, embed, edit, default is view
Param: page: the page number to list, default is 1
Param: per_page: the number of posts per page to list, default is 10
Param: author_ids: a list of comma separated author ids, default is None
Param: search_query: the search query to filter posts, default is None
Param: statuses: a comma separated list of statuses to filter posts, default is publish. Valid statuses are: publish, future, draft, pending, private, trash, auto-draft, inherit, request-pending, request-confirmed, request-failed, request-completed
Param: publish_after: the date and time to filter posts published after, default is None
Param: publish_before: the date and time to filter posts published before, default is None
Param: modified_after: the date and time to filter posts modified after, default is None
Param: modified_before: the date and time to filter posts modified before, default is None
Param: order: the order to sort posts, must be one of: asc, desc, default is desc.

#!/usr/bin/env python3 ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/main.py ListPosts

---
Name: Retrieve Post
Description: Retrieve a post in wordpress site
Credential: ./credential
Share Context: Wordpress Context
Param: post_id: the id of the post
Param: context: the context of the post, must be one of: view, embed, edit, default is view
Param: password: the password of the post, default is None

#!/usr/bin/env python3 ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/main.py RetrievePost

---
Name: Create Post
Description: Create a post in user'swordpress site
Credential: ./credential
Share Context: Wordpress Context
Param: title: the title of the post
Param: content: the content of the post
Param: status: the status of the post, must be one of: publish, future, draft, pending, private
Param: comment_status: the comment status of the post, must be one of: open, closed. default is open
Param: sticky: whether the post is sticky to the top of the page, default is false
Param: password: the password of the post, default is None
Param: slug: the slug of the post, default is None
Param: date: the date of the post, default is None. Must be a valid ISO 8601 date string, in the format of YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS, or YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS+HH:MM for timezone aware date. If the date is a future date, the post will be scheduled to be published at that time.
Param: format: the format of the post to create, must be one of: standard, aside, chat, gallery, link, image, quote, status, video, audio. default is standard
Param: author_id: the id of the author of the post. If not provided, the current user will be used.
Param: excerpt: the excerpt of the post, default is None
Param: ping_status: the ping status of the post, must be one of: open, closed. default is open

#!/usr/bin/env python3 ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/main.py CreatePost

---
Name: Update Post
Description: Update a post in user's wordpress site. Only the fields that are provided will be updated.
Credential: ./credential
Share Context: Wordpress Context
Param: post_id: the id of the post to update
Param: title: the title of the post
Param: content: the content of the post
Param: status: the status of the post, must be one of: publish, future, draft, pending, private
Param: comment_status: the comment status of the post, must be one of: open, closed
Param: sticky: whether the post is sticky to the top of the page
Param: password: the password of the post
Param: slug: the slug of the post
Param: date: the date of the post, default is None. Must be a valid ISO 8601 date string, in the format of YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS, or YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS+HH:MM for timezone aware date. If the date is a future date, the post will be scheduled to be published at that time.
Param: format: the format of the post to create, must be one of: standard, aside, chat, gallery, link, image, quote, status, video, audio. default is standard
Param: author_id: the id of the author of the post
Param: excerpt: the excerpt of the post
Param: ping_status: the ping status of the post, must be one of: open, closed

#!/usr/bin/env python3 ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/main.py UpdatePost

---
Name: Delete Post
Description: Delete a post in user's wordpress site
Credential: ./credential
Share Context: Wordpress Context
Param: post_id: the id of the post to delete
Param: force: whether to force delete the post, default is false. If true, the post will be deleted permanently, instead of being moved to trash.

#!/usr/bin/env python3 ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/main.py DeletePost

